 Trading activities on the floor of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) yesterday further closed downswing, as the overall market performance indices dropped marginally by 0.02 per cent.
Transactions on the stock market had the previous day also closed on the negative trajectory.
However, at the close of trading yesterday, the All-Share Index dropped by 7.41 basis points or 0.02 per cent to close at 29,765.31 index points as against 29.772.72 recorded the previous day, while the market capitalisation of equities depreciated by N3 billion from N13.119 trillion the previous day to N13.116 trillion.
Meanwhile, a turnover of 275.5 million shares exchanged in 3,977 deals was recorded in the day’s trading.
The banking sub- sector was the most active (measured by turnover volume) with 94.6 million shares exchanged by investors in 833 deals.
Volume in the sub-sector was largely driven by the activities in the shares of Sterling Bank Plc and GTB Plc.
Premium sub-sector boosted by the activities in the shares of Lafarge Africa Plc and Access Bank Plc followed with a turnover of 94.4 million shares in 1,239 deals.
The number of gainers at the close of trading session was 25, while decliners closed at 14.
Further analysis of the day’s trading showed that Wapco Plc topped the gainers’ table with 9.95 per cent to close at N10.50 per share, while Linkage Assurance Plc followed with 8.93 per cent to close at 61 kobo per share. Thomas Wyatt Plc gain of 8.82 per cent to close at 37 kobo per share.
On the flip side, C and I Leasing Plc led the losers’ chart with a drop of 10 per cent to close at N5.67 per share. Forte Oil Plc tailed with a loss of 9.96 per cent to close at N31.20 per share. while Wapic Insurance Plc dropped by 8.89 per cent to close at 41kobo per share.